comment.body:
I would have assumed that `rule_head_general_refs` implies `rule_head_ref_string_prefixes` and if users wanted to prevent the use of variables at arbitrary locations they would specify only `rule_head_ref_string_prefixes`. 

@johanfylling  I agree with your concern about breaking an already established contract for `rule_head_ref_string_prefixes`. But do we know the impact of this if we changed the behavior? 

Longer term  `rule_head_general_refs` implying `rule_head_ref_string_prefixes` would be better imo. If we document and promote this well enough we can prevent any surprise behaviors I think.
